<br />
Gandalf, the Old Fell and The Nine Servants by Christopher Niska  </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">Ok here we go.<br />
I bet with 4 burdens (So far Ive won all bets). Then I start with Gandalf and The Prancing Pony to add a burden and play Aragorn. I Move on to site 3. Hide cards help here a lot. The free peoples deck is very simple you just go slow if you like but I prefer to win so I&#39;d make it to site 6 on turn 3.<br />
The shadow is fierce and high str for overwhelming and adding burdens, finally killing off the whole party. If the Ringwraiths are played right you won&#39;t get past them.<br />
<br />
-- Expl. of Some Cards --<br />
<br />
Sam - Removes burdens of course.<br />
<br />
Aragorn + Bow - Archers down anything that moves, combined with Strenght of Spirit you can Archer up to 5 wounds in one turn.<br />
<br />
Aragorn + A Ranger&#39;s Versality - This is so nice against i.e. Ulaire Enquea. You spot a Aragorn and do 3 wounds to Enquea so he cant use the gametext anymore. Very nice against Uruks and Nazguls.<br />
<br />
Aragorn + Merry or Sam - Heal one wound per turn.<br />
<br />
Sting + Glamdring - Reduces the twilight between sites to 0 if playing vs an Orc deck.<br />
<br />
Sleep, Caradhras - Anti-Nazgul discards all Black Breaths, Blade Tips, etc.<br />
<br />
The One Ring, Isildurs Bane - I dont want to add burdens, but I could use a wound.<br />
<br />
--<br />
<br />
I think that&#39;s about it. Try it, I doubt that you wounldn&#39;t like it.<br />
<br />
